  "response": "Here are some ways junior high school students can earn money:\n\n1. Babysitting\n- Watching younger children for neighbors or family friends\n- Requires responsibility and basic childcare skills\n\n2. Pet sitting/Dog walking\n- Taking care of pets while owners are away\n- Walking dogs in the neighborhood\n\n3. Lawn care and yard work\n- Mowing lawns\n- Raking leaves\n- Weeding gardens\n- Helping neighbors with outdoor chores\n\n4. Tutoring\n- Helping younger students with homework\n- Teaching subjects they excel in\n\n5. Selling handmade crafts\n- Making and selling artwork\n- Creating jewelry or other crafts online or at local markets\n\n6. Car washing\n- Offering car wash services to neighbors and family friends\n\n7. Recycling\n- Collecting and returning bottles and cans\n- Helping neighbors sort recyclables\n\n8. Online tasks\n- Taking online surveys\n- Doing small digital tasks on platforms like Amazon Mechanical Turk\n- Creating content on YouTube (with parental supervision)\n\n9. Helping with household chores\n- Doing extra chores for parents or relatives for payment\n\n10. Social media assistance\n- Helping small local businesses with social media management\n\nRemember to always get parental permission and guidance when pursuing these opportunities.",
